reviews.review_text:
Wow! where have you been my whole life? I loved this fall tour, but have never deleved into this part of the tour. My bad. I heard the  Two Soldiers Jam last  night on grradio awaiting the second set of MSG, and I was like wow!
The first set is amazing and Brent and the entire Band rip Hey Pocky Way and the set  just  takes off from there. Super version of Push and the rest of the set is stellar. The Cassidy is exceptional and the Deal rages.
 Set two starts off with a  secial  guest and they once again rip into it and soon they hit their stride and deliver a fun version.
 The China Cat  takes  alittle  time to sync up but once they do they explode in Rider. Very hot.
The Samson  continues this and then a beautiful  reading of Terrapin.
The paot space is  excellent and the band rages big time. Brent is on fire and Jerry is takin no prisoners either. It is all played with passion and intensity. For you Stella Lovers this one is a  true  gem. Sugar Mag rages and a great sunshine day dream too. Jerry flubs  a few verses of Baby Blue but it is a  powerful  version none the less. 5 for the post space and first set.

Two Soldiers Jam 1) Jams are usually longer than 51 seconds

2) It sure sounds like Playin' to me. Right before Jerry starts up the Playin' riff he is noodling.

Cabin Boy? Great, I have been looking for this show for years to find the riff that jerry played during space.  When i was there, I likened it to an "irish jig", and had not heard it before.  A reviewer references it as Cabin Boy"  Makes sense.  My question is, when did Jerry play this riff previously, or subsequenty during space.  I have not come across it otherwise.

Great Recording This is a fantastic recording. I was at this show. The Deal to close the first set was one for the ages. Jerry just went nuts. I remember Spencer Davis joining in on Gimme Some Lovin. That was cool. I was sitting right behind the taper's section. The China-Rider was nice as well.
